Export IDBIndexMetadata so the (separately-linked) miniblink_host dylib can
construct it when RESTORING a persisted IndexedDB database with secondary indexes.

Its sibling IDBObjectStoreMetadata is already MODULES_EXPORT; IDBIndexMetadata is
not — almost certainly an oversight, since both are public metadata structs in the
same header with public ctors/Create(). Without the export, IDBIndexMetadata::
Create()/the ctors don't resolve from our dylib, so mb_indexeddb.cc had to SKIP
persisting any database that has an index. This one-line export lets it reconstruct
index metadata on load. No behavior change for the donor build (just visibility).

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/indexeddb/idb_metadata.h b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/indexeddb/idb_metadata.h
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/indexeddb/idb_metadata.h
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/indexeddb/idb_metadata.h
@@ -44,7 +44,7 @@
 // these objects form a tree with the hierarchy shown below.
 //     IDBDatabaseMetadata -> IDBObjectStoreMetadata -> IDBIndexMetadata

-class IDBIndexMetadata : public RefCounted<IDBIndexMetadata> {
+class MODULES_EXPORT IDBIndexMetadata : public RefCounted<IDBIndexMetadata> {
   USING_FAST_MALLOC(IDBIndexMetadata);

  public:
